## Proof Anti-Patterns (Never Do This)

### ❌ Hand-Waving:
```latex
\begin{proof}
It is obvious that... The rest is straightforward. ∎
\end{proof}
```

### ❌ Proof by Authority:
```latex
\begin{proof}
According to [famous mathematician], this must be true. ∎
\end{proof}
```

### ❌ Proof by Intimidation:
```latex
\begin{proof}
The proof is left as a trivial exercise for the reader. ∎
\end{proof}
```

### ❌ Circular Reasoning:
```latex
\begin{proof}
A is true because B is true.
B is true because A is true. ∎
\end{proof}
```

### ❌ Proof by Example:
```latex
\begin{theorem}
For all n ∈ ℕ, property P(n) holds.
\end{theorem}

\begin{proof}
For n = 1, 2, 3, we have verified P(n). ∎
\end{proof}
```
